<arggraph id="micro_b045">
  <edu id="e1"><![CDATA[By purchasing illegally acquired tax data of citizens,]]></edu>
  <edu id="e2"><![CDATA[the state is not only turning itself into a felon,]]></edu>
  <edu id="e3"><![CDATA[but it is paying criminals, too.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e4"><![CDATA[Besides, the purchase of such CDs is unnecessary today,]]></edu>
  <edu id="e5"><![CDATA[as,]]></edu>
  <edu id="e6"><![CDATA[due to changed terms of business,]]></edu>
  <edu id="e7"><![CDATA[many banks urge their customers to turn themselves in.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e8"><![CDATA[Acquiring CDs with tax data of tax delinquents is therefore out of the question.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e9"><![CDATA[It is indisputable, however, that by purchasing such data the state increases the pressure on tax evaders to turn themselves in.]]></edu>
